description:
&lt;p&gt;Camden &amp; Islington mental health and social care trust are seeking to appoint a bright and enthusiastic clinician to this fixed term locum Consultant post in a very well established Liaison Service and Old Age inpatient ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This exciting opportunity has arisen as the incumbent consultant is going on maternity leave. It is available for one year in the first instance however candidates available for shorter period and or part time are encourage to also apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is based between the Liaison department at Whittington Hospital and Garnet Ward at Highgate Mental Health Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is available as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is subject to the annual job-planning and appraisal process as agreed under the NHS Consultant contract. Inner London weighting supplement applies. Both posts are complimented by full MDT teams including middle grade and junior doctor support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is secretarial cover with shared office/administration facilities provided within the team office base. They will be supported in pursuing appropriate continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust became a Foundation Trust in February 2008 and continues as a mental health/social care organisation. It has well established links with the United Royal Free and University college London medical schools and the North London Junior and higher Psychiatric training schemes. Camden and Islington are exciting multicultural inner-city boroughs just on the edge of the City of London and Highgate mental health centre is based close to the varied shops, cafes and cultural amenities in the Highgate area as well as Archway. The Trust is a small and friendly organisation and mentoring is potentially available for first time Consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are expected to have MRCPsych or equivalent and substantial approved training experience in psychiatry , ideally up to CCT level, fulfilling criteria for the Consultant contract .Full GMC registration and a current GMC license to practise are essential. Possession of Section 12(2) approval is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications should be made through NHSJobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews are currently likely to be conducted via virtual video conferencing media at a date to be confirmed ... &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Dr Suzanne Joels clinical Director at suzanne.joels@candi.nhs.uk or Dr Koye Odutoye, Deputy Medical Director on koye.odutoye@candi.nhs.uk or 07775583640&lt;/p&gt;
